body:
The conversion script has parameters like [op_block_list](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxconverter-common/blob/68ef94743672f426bb8726bb796db96522b17239/onnxconverter_common/float16.py#L91) that you can use to exclude operators like FusedConv. 

I think the default list is not comprehensive: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxconverter-common/blob/68ef94743672f426bb8726bb796db96522b17239/onnxconverter_common/float16.py#L82-L86
So you're actually saying that onnxruntime doesn't support fp16 inference of simple old resnet ?

This is also happening for NVIDIA Jasper https://catalog.ngc.nvidia.com/orgs/nvidia/models/jasper_pyt_onnx_fp16_amp

>'Internal: onnx runtime error 6: Exception during initialization: /workspace/onnxruntime/onnxruntime/core/optimizer/transformer_memcpy.cc:374 bool onnxruntime::TransformerMemcpyImpl::ProcessInitializers(const onnxruntime::KernelRegistryManager&, const InitializedTensorSet&) status.IsOK() was false. Failed to find kernel for FusedConv(1) (node Conv_17). Op with name (Conv_17) and type (FusedConv) kernel is not supported in CUDAExecutionProvider. Encountered following errors: (Found kernel for Op with name (Conv_17) and type (FusedConv) in the supported version range (node_version: 1 kernel start version: 1 kernel_end_version: 2147483647). However the types are incompatible. This op has been implemented only for the following types (tensor(float),), but the node in the model has the following type (tensor(float16))\n)\n'

I think his might be a bug introduced in onnxruntime v1.11.0.
I used onnxrutnime v1.10.0 and v1.11.0 on same scripts. v1.11.0 produced same error like @[hyperfraise](https://github.com/hyperfraise) has, but v1.10.0 runs without any error. Not sure if v1.11.1 fix this.

issue.title: Fp16 Resnet50 Model cannot run in cuda provider.

labels.name: ep:CUDA
labels.description: issues related to the CUDA execution provider

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
Following codes import pretrained resnet50 model from torchvision and use onnxmltools tools to convert into half type model, then run on cuda EP.
Codes can run without any error in onnxruntime v1.10, but can't run after onnxruntime v1.11
Testing environments are all the same (including dependency packages' versions).

```
import io
import numpy as np
import torchvision

from torch import nn
import torch.utils.model_zoo as model_zoo
import torch.onnx
import torch.nn as nn
import torch.nn.init as init
import onnx
from onnx import load_model, save_model
import onnxruntime
from onnxmltools.utils import float16_converter

torch.manual_seed(0)
np.random.seed(0)
torch_model = torchvision.models.resnet50(pretrained=True).eval()
batch_size = 10  

map_location = lambda storage, loc: storage
if torch.cuda.is_available():
    map_location = None

torch_model = torch_model.cuda().half()
data = np.random.rand(batch_size,3,224,224).astype(np.float32)
x = torch.from_numpy(data).cuda().half()
torch_out = torch_model(x)

torch.onnx.export(torch_model,               
                  x,                        
                  "resnet.onnx",             
                  export_params=True,       
                  opset_version=10,          
                  do_constant_folding=True,  
                  input_names = ['input'],   
                  output_names = ['output'], 
                  dynamic_axes={'input' : {0 : 'batch_size'},    
                                'output' : {0 : 'batch_size'}})
onnx_fp32_model = load_model("resnet.onnx")
onnx_fp16_model = float16_converter.convert_float_to_float16(onnx_fp32_model,keep_io_types=True)
save_model(onnx_fp16_model, "resnet_fp16.onnx")

def to_numpy(tensor):
    return tensor.detach().cpu().numpy() if tensor.requires_grad else tensor.cpu().numpy()

ort_session = onnxruntime.SessionOptions()
ort_session.graph_optimization_level = onnxruntime.GraphOptimizationLevel.ORT_ENABLE_EXTENDED
session = onnxruntime.InferenceSession("resnet_fp16.onnx", ort_session,providers=['CUDAExecutionProvider'])
ort_inputs = {session.get_inputs()[0].name: to_numpy(x)}
ort_outs = session.run(None, ort_inputs)

print("diff is:",to_numpy(torch_out)-ort_outs[0])
np.testing.assert_allclose(to_numpy(torch_out), ort_outs[0], rtol=1e-03, atol=1e-05)
print("Exported model has been tested with ONNXRuntime, and the result looks good!")
```
Error message in ORT v1.11.0:
`
onnxruntime.capi.onnxruntime_pybind11_state.RuntimeException: [ONNXRuntimeError] : 6 : RUNTIME_EXCEPTION : Exception during initialization: /home/cheng.chen/git/onnxruntime/onnxruntime/core/optimizer/transformer_memcpy.cc:374 bool onnxruntime::TransformerMemcpyImpl::ProcessInitializers(const onnxruntime::KernelRegistryManager&, const InitializedTensorSet&) status.IsOK() was false. Failed to find kernel for FusedConv(1) (node Conv_8). Op with name (Conv_8) and type (FusedConv) kernel is not supported in CUDAExecutionProvider. Encountered following errors: (Found kernel for Op with name (Conv_8) and type (FusedConv) in the supported version range (node_version: 1 kernel start version: 1 kernel_end_version: 2147483647). However the types are incompatible. This op has been implemented only for the following types (tensor(float),), but the node in the model has the following type (tensor(float16)) 
`

**Urgency**
Resnet50 is a simple and basic model, so same error might happen in other complex models.

**System information**
- OS Platform and Distribution: Linux Ubuntu 16.04
- ONNX Runtime installed from (source or binary): binary
- ONNX Runtime version: v1.11.0
- Python version: Python3.7
- CUDA/cuDNN version: CUDA 11.4, cudnn 8
- GPU model and memory: Nvidia GTX1080Ti

**To Reproduce**
Python3 to run above codes

**Expected behavior**
Exported model has been tested with ONNXRuntime, and the result looks good!


**Additional context**
This might be same issue to [#11768](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/11768)
I tried method like https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/11768#issuecomment-1150221102 says, but still no pass.
Not sure if this is related to the onnxmltools.
Tried to debug, found this might relate to the graph that ORT modified internally. In v1.10, no FusedConv Nodes are added, but in v1.11, they are added. However, there are no FusedConv Op implemention for half type. Per https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/onnxruntime/contrib_ops/cuda/fused_conv.cc#L117

issue.title: Add data type check in ConvAddRelu fusion

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**: 

The CUDA (and the CPU EP) only supports the float type for FusedConv.  When the ConvActivationFusion got split into SelectActionTransformers (https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/commit/9e7d7a9e97c979c3b32fac4d54324e3f9c6b1d40#diff-e6b85539fe82c4b67655ba0f67140ad12548665d5633f820703e7c9cff0a87e2), the Conv+Add+Relu transformer didn't have the data type check duplicated in it - the Conv+Activation tranformer retained the original check before refactoring.

Additionally the data type check should also cover the CPU EP (https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/6653#discussion_r574958591)

**Motivation and Context**
Fixes https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/12045 and https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/11768
-This is a regression introduced in 1.11.

Fixes https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/11476  (No double type support in CPU FusedConv )

body: Thanks guys. I understand my issue is basically dupplicate, so I'll close it and I hope this is soon resolved.
